## Module: Cells as the Basis of Life

### Overview
This module covers key concepts in Cells as the Basis of Life for the HSC biology course.

### Topics
- Topic 1 in Cells as the Basis of Life
- Topic 2 in Cells as the Basis of Life

### Learning Outcomes

Students will develop skills to:

- Identify and explain key concepts related to Cells as the Basis of Life
- Analyse and interpret information related to Cells as the Basis of Life
- Apply understanding of Cells as the Basis of Life to solve problems
- Evaluate arguments and perspectives related to Cells as the Basis of Life
- Communicate understanding of Cells as the Basis of Life using appropriate terminology

### Key Concepts

This module introduces the following key concepts:

- Fundamental principles of Cells as the Basis of Life
- Core terminology and definitions
- Theoretical frameworks
- Practical applications
- Critical analysis techniques

